Constructor Detail

TextureHelper

public TextureHelper(java.lang.String blenderVersion,
                     boolean fixUpAxis)
This constructor parses the given blender version and stores the result. It creates noise generator and texture generators.

Parameters:
blenderVersion - the version read from the blend file
fixUpAxis - a variable that indicates if the Y asxis is the UP axis or not
Method Detail

getTexture

public Texture getTexture(Structure tex,
                          BlenderContext blenderContext)
                   throws BlenderFileException
This class returns a texture read from the file or from packed blender data. The returned texture has the name set to the value of its blender type.

Parameters:
tex - texture structure filled with data
blenderContext - the blender context
Returns:
the texture that can be used by JME engine
Throws:
BlenderFileException - this exception is thrown when the blend file structure is somehow invalid or corrupted

blendTexture

public Texture blendTexture(float[] materialColor,
                            Texture texture,
                            float[] color,
                            float affectFactor,
                            int blendType,
                            boolean neg,
                            BlenderContext blenderContext)
This method blends the given texture with material color and the defined color in 'map to' panel. As a result of this method a new texture is created. The input texture is NOT.

Parameters:
materialColor - the material diffuse color
texture - the texture we use in blending
color - the color defined for the texture
affectFactor - the factor that the color affects the texture (value form 0.0 to 1.0)
blendType - the blending type
blenderContext - the blender context
Returns:
new texture that was created after the blending

mergeTextures

public Texture mergeTextures(java.util.List<Texture> sources,
                             MaterialContext materialContext)
This method merges the given textures. The result texture has no alpha factor (is always opaque).

Parameters:
sources - the textures to be merged
materialContext - the context of the material
Returns:
merged textures
